cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.SI 

This paper is primarily focused on the networking aspects of CCN and proposes a new access control scheme for CCN. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security issues related to access control, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the computational, storage, and bandwidth costs of the proposed scheme, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also proposes a flexible design that allows producers to specify and enforce any type of content access control, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the mutual trust framework between producers and consumers, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
